how does a second interview go what is it for i had my first interview june th and my second one will be monday aug they have been conducting job bids with current employees and called me today for nd interview this is in a factory so does this mean i have the job what will they ask and want to know i am not working now will they ask me why i havent found something else and what should i say cause there really isnt much going on around here work wise one more thing they are hiring for several positions on second and third shift at two different locations lots of positions available second interviews can be used for a few reasons in a large factory with a lot of positions open they may have already decided who they are going to hire but not have made the decision on where they will be placed some times the second or third interview work as sort of levels in a plant it is important that the guys on the same shift can work well together the second interview may be with the shift supervisor to see if you will fit with his crew the bottom line is that there is no definite answer you may not know until you walk in the door what will be discussed i suggest you get to the interview early and listen to the whispers be confidant but not cocky about how you would be a great asset to the company the website below may offer more assistance Social rule Time Out of Mind The Apprentice 2 Call centre DisneySpeak Economic inequality Job interview Principal-agent problem Plame affair Outsourcing Unemployment Expert system Keynesian economics Military opposition to the Reconciliation, Tolerance, and Unity Bill (Fiji) Productive and unproductive labour Offshoring Roswell UFO incident Peter Arnett Ra (board game) Single Convention on Narcotic Drugs Steve Jobs 2005 trial of Michael Jackson The Ersatz Elevator Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Microeconomics Exploitation National Kidney Foundation Singapore Employment Crew Exploration Vehicle Software engineering STS-59 Anarchi